cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.IR

This paper proposes a taxonomy for categorizing 360° videos based on moving objects and camera motion, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also analyzes viewport patterns, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) or computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the dataset and analysis of viewer feedback could potentially fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
